						               													<description>Good Guess is the perfect casual party game for friends and families, for teams and individuals. It&amp;rsquo;s part riddle, part trivia and part just sound logical reasoning.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;We love this trivia game because it stimulates more conversation than (dare we say) any game ever!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Clues come one at a time - the first team to guess correctly earns points. Use wild cards to pull a fast one on a leader who thinks they&amp;rsquo;re cruising to victory. With for ways to play ranging from fast-paced to highly collaborative, it&amp;rsquo;s a great addition to any dinner party, getaway, family evening or long car ride.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Our family created this game over 10 years ago after we couldn&amp;rsquo;t find a simple, fun and stimulating game to play in the evenings. We love it because it stimulates conversation, stories and all sorts of goodness that contributes rather than detracts from a great evening. We intentionally made the game play simple. We eliminated the need for game pieces, a game board, die and, of course, complicated instructions that bewilder and frustrate.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The clue cards are loaded with astonishing facts about everyday people, places and things that are certain to entertain. Our rule of thumb was: the clues needed to make the folks playing the game excited about guessing and learning the answer. Did you know, for example, that Harry Houdini died one week after being buried alive?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
